Aquatic Leadership
Bronze Cross
The Lifesaving Society’s Bronze Cross begins the transition from lifesaving to lifeguarding and prepares candidates for responsibilities as assistant lifeguards. Candidates strengthen and expand their lifesaving skills and begin to apply the principles and techniques of active surveillance in aquatic facilities. Bronze Cross emphasizes the importance of teamwork and communication in preventing and responding to aquatic emergencies. Bronze Cross is a prerequisite for advanced training in the Society’s National Lifeguard and leadership certification programs. Pre-requisite: Bronze Medallion.

Bronze Medallion
Bronze Medallion challenges the candidate both mentally and physically. Judgment, knowledge, skill and fitness – the four components of water rescue – form the basis of Bronze Medallion training. Candidates acquire the assessment and problem-solving skills needed to make good decisions in, on, and around the water. Bronze Medallion is a prerequisite for assistant lifeguard training in Bronze Cross. Pre-requisites: 13yrs of age or Bronze Star and swimming ability at a Swimmer 9 level.

Bronze Medallion/ Cross Combo
The Lifesaving Society’s Bronze Medallion & Cross Combo course offers a streamlined pathway for individuals aiming to become certified lifeguards. Designed for those aged 13 and older, or those holding a Bronze Star certification, this combined program merges the comprehensive training of both Bronze Medallion and Bronze Cross into a single, intensive course. Participants will develop advanced lifesaving skills, including effective victim recognition, two-rescuer rescues, spinal injury management, and active surveillance techniques in aquatic facilities. The course emphasizes teamwork, communication, and decision-making in high-pressure situations, preparing candidates for the responsibilities of assistant lifeguards. The course comprises both classroom and water activities, requiring 100% attendance and participation. Students are evaluated until the final day of the combo course. Successful completion of the course earns participants both the Bronze Medallion and Bronze Cross certifications and serves as a prerequisite for the National Lifeguard program. Successful completion of this course is worth TWO (2) Grade 11 Credits. Prerequisites: Minimum 13 years of age OR Bronze Star certification, minimum Swim Level 6 recommended.. Course fee will appear at checkout.
Bronze Medallion/ Cross combo

Bronze Star
Bronze Star is a pre-Bronze Medallion training program that helps to prepare candidates for success in Bronze Medallion. The Lifesaving Society’s Bronze Star develops swimming proficiency, lifesaving skill and personal fitness. Candidates refine their stroke mechanics, acquire self-rescue skills, and apply fitness principles in training workouts. Bronze Star is excellent preparation for success in Bronze Medallion and provides a fun introduction to lifesaving sport.

Camp Babysitter Training 11-15yrs
Become a Child Safe certified babysitter. This camp covers the responsibilities of a babysitter, basic childcare skills, stages of play and development, safety tips , what to do in case of an emergency, first aid, mealtimes, diapering babies and other related skills. Each student will receive a Child Safe Canada Babysitter manual - $10 manual fee added to price at check-out Must be 11yrs old by the last class, attend all sessions and meet competency requirements to receive the certification. Camp Forms can be completed online on your child's NVRC account. Visit www.nvrc.ca/camps to learn more.

Camp Byte School Age
Byte Camp makes tech education fun for kids. Every summer they cover topics in coding and game design, music and video editing, animation, 3D modelling, and more with the goal of each child designing, building, and producing their own awesome take-home project. Since 2003 over 13,000 kids have come through their programs, with their number one priority being to ensure kids have the best week of their summer! And don't worry parents, they'll be taking breaks throughout the day to take part in outdoor games and activities! Camp Forms can be completed online on your child's NVRC account. Visit www.nvrc.ca/camps to learn more. Please read the notes on your Registration Confirmation for important information regarding our camp services.

Certifications and Leadership
Babysitter Training 11-15yrs
Become a Child Safe certified babysitter. This course covers the responsibilities of a babysitter, basic childcare skills, stages of play and development, safety tips , what to do in case of an emergency, first aid, mealtimes, diapering babies and other related skills. Must be 11yrs old by the last class, attend all sessions and meet competency requirements to receive the certification. Each student will receive a Child Safe Canada Babysitter manual - $10 manual fee added to price at check-out

Staff is available for guidance and support. Please communicate with your child these responsibilities. $10 manual fee added to price at check-out.

Home Alone 10yrs+
An interactive safety training program for youths ages 10+. This program prepares youth for the important step of staying home alone safely. This course teaches safety, first aid, and comfort skills through interactive games and role-playing. Staying home alone isn’t an event, it’s a process – students will come away with knowledge, skills and more confidence. A $5 manual fee will be added to price at check-out

Delbrook Licensed Preschool
Our holistic approach and play-based program fosters children’s physical, emotional, social, creative and intellectual growth through four key approaches: well-being & belonging, exploration & creativity, languages & literacy, and social responsibility & diversity. Registration for the 2025/2026 school year can be done online or by calling 604-983-6530. Prices listed reflect the total cost for the school year in full and a monthly scheduled payment option is also available. For more detailed information about NVRC preschools, please visit nvrc.ca/preschool. Martial Arts
Ground & Stand-up Martial Arts Techniques: All Levels 13yrs+
Get fit learning self-defence skills. Activities include punching bags, focus mitts, resistance training, and partner and individual work. Learn standing and ground skills such as: blocking, counter-attacks, locking, unlocking and combination techniques. Beginners welcome. No uniform required. Program instructed by International Top Karate (Mike H.)

Karate Early Years
Children learn basic karate skills such as proper stance and posture in a fun environment that promotes self-confidence and traditional values. The focus is on child development skills such as developing basic gross motor skills and concentration skills. This program prepares children to move into our schoolage program when they are 6yrs old. Program instructed by International Top Karate. Please see the registration confirmation attached to your receipt for more details about this program.

Swimmer 1 (6-12yrs)
These beginners will become comfortable jumping into the water with and without a PFD. They’ll learn how to open their eyes, exhale and hold their breath underwater. Floats, glides and kicking skills are introduced. (Equivalent to Stage 1A)

Swimmer 6 (6-12yrs)
These swimmers will become proficient at deep water skills including stride entries and compact jumps. They’ll develop lifesaving kicks such as eggbeater and scissor kick. Breaststroke, front crawl, and back crawl are further developed. Head-up swims, interval training and a 300m workout develop strength and endurance. (Equivalent to Stage 2B)

Swimmer 7 - Rookie Patrol (8-12yrs)
Swimmers continue developing front crawl, back crawl and breaststroke. Swimmers develop individual fitness to meet a timed 100m swim and 350m workout. Water proficiency skills include swimming with clothes, ready position, and feet-first/head-first surface dives. Demonstrating the ability to conduct a primary assessment and calling EMS are included as first aid skills. Victim recognition and throwing assists are other key elements of the program. (Equivalent to Advanced Stage 2B or beginner Canadian Swim Patrol)

Swimmer 8 - Ranger Patrol (8-12yrs)
Ranger Patrol enhances capability in the water including stride entries and underwater, forward and backward somersaults. Swimmers learn lifesaving sport skills with a lifesaving stroke medley, timed object support and a non-contact rescue with a buoyant aid. Eggbeater kick and increased fitness levels are developed to meet a 200m timed swim. First aid focuses on unconscious victims and obstructed airway procedures. (Equivalent to Canadian Swim Patrol)

Swimmer 9 - Star Patrol (8-12yrs)
Star Patrol challenges swimmers with a 300m timed swim, 600m workout and a 25m object carry. Strokes are continued to be refined. Lifesaving skills include use of rescue aids, defense methods, victim removals and supporting a victim in shallow water. First aid focuses on treatment of bone or joint injuries and respiratory emergencies. Once complete, swimmers register into Bronze Star. (Equivalent to Stage 3 and Stage 4)
